      <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
	<p>
	  Success! By <persName key="pers:Uṣavadāta">Usabhadāta</persName>, 
	  the son of <persName key="pers:Dinīka">Dinīka</persName> and
	  son-in-law of the king, the Khaharāta, the Kṣatrapa
	  <persName key="pers:Nahapāna">Nahapāna</persName>,—who have three-hundred-thousand
	  cows, who made gifts of gold and a tīrtha on the river
	  <placeName key="pl:Bārṇāsā">Bārṇāsā</placeName>, who gave to
	  [the Devas] and the Brāhmaṇas sixteen villages, who at the
	  pure tīrtha <placeName key="pl:Prabhāsa">Prabhāsa</placeName> gave 
	  eight wives to the Brāhmaṇas, and who also fed annually a 
	  hundred-thousand (Brāhmaṇas),—there has been given in the village
	  of <placeName key="pl:Karajika">Karajika</placeName> for
	  the support of the ascetics living in the caves at 
	  <placeName key="pl:Valūraka">Valūraka</placeName>
	  without any distinction of sect or origin, for all who
	  would keep the varṣa (there).
	</p>
